The paper deals with training recurrent neural networks (RNNs) on long sequence tasks, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper proposes a mean field theory of signal propagation in LSTMs and GRUs, which is a technique used in deep learning and falls under the category of neural networks. The paper also discusses optimization of initialization hyperparameters, which is a common technique used in optimization algorithms and falls under the category of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
